<body>
    <h1>1.2.3 Adding Keywords</h1>

    <p>
        The minilang keywords, or reserved words, consist of strings for the statement selection, types and Boolean literals 
        that are mapped to the corresponding tokens.
    </p>

    <p>
        The keyword file syntax is described in <a href="../../syntax/lexer.html#keyword-file-syntax">this</a> document.
    </p>

    <p>
        To add keywords to the minilang language:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>
            Right-click your project in the Solution Explorer and select 'Add | New Item...'.
        </li>
        <li>
            Select Visual C++ | Utility | Text File (.txt) item and name the file <span class="mono">minilang.keyword</span>.
        </li>
        <li>
            Add the following code to the keyword file:<br />
			<ref file="ref/minilang.keyword.div"/>
        </li>
    </ul>
</body>
</html>